SIMPLE: grappling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grappling
<hw>Grap"pling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
laying fast ho1d of; also, that by which anything is seized and held, a
grapnel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A grapple; a struggle. A match for yards in fight,
in grappling for the bear.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Grappling iron</b></col>, <cd>a hooked iron used for
grappling and holding fast a vessel or other object.</cd> --
<col><b>Grappling tongs</b></col>, <cd>broad-mouthed tongs for gathering
oysters.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grapsoid</ent>⟦br⟧
